<subSubSection id="C331653CB937E5053A948849FE16FE8C" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="377" pageId="10" pageNumber="376" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9436B7B937E5043A948849FD4BF837" blockId="10.[151,1436,1764,2043]" pageId="10" pageNumber="376">
<emphasis id="B95FEAA5B937E5043A948849FEE9F8EE" bold="true" box="[199,317,1801,1827]" pageId="10" pageNumber="376">Remarks:</emphasis>
Like 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B4D34B937E5043B2C8849FE22F8EF" authority="Swanson, 2021" authorityName="Swanson" authorityYear="2021" box="[383,502,1801,1826]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Heza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="376" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="graziae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B95FEAA5B937E5043B2C8849FE22F8EF" box="[383,502,1801,1826]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="376">H. graziae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B95FEAA5B937E5043BAE8849FD83F8EE" bold="true" box="[509,599,1801,1827]" pageId="10" pageNumber="376">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26C57DEB937E5043BAE8849FD83F8EE" box="[509,599,1801,1827]" pageId="10" pageNumber="376" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, the short, sharp armature of the anterior pronotal lobe results in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B4D34B937E5043F678849FF68F88B" authority="Swanson, 2021" authorityName="Swanson" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Heza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="376" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridipes" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B95FEAA5B937E5043F678849FF68F88B" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="376">H. viridipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B95FEAA5B937E5043A96886DFECBF88A" bold="true" box="[197,287,1837,1863]" pageId="10" pageNumber="376">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26C57DEB937E5043A96886DFECBF88A" box="[197,287,1837,1863]" pageId="10" pageNumber="376" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
keying to couplet # 
<quantity id="4CD39B52B937E5043850886DFDE8F88B" box="[515,572,1836,1863]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.842" pageId="10" pageNumber="376" unit="in" value="23.0">23 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="EFBA4B46B937E5043817886CFCFDF88A" author="Maldonado" box="[580,809,1836,1863]" pageId="10" pageNumber="376" pagination="403 - 433" refId="ref8630" refString="Maldonado C., J. (1976) The genus Heza (Hemiptera: Reduviidae). Journal of Agriculture of the University of Puerto Rico, 60 (3), 403 - 433. https: // doi. org / 10.46429 / jaupr. v 60 i 3.10533" type="journal article" year="1976">Maldonado’s (1976)</bibRefCitation>
key. Unlike 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B4D34B937E50439E8886DFBE6F88B" authority="Swanson, 2021" authorityName="Swanson" authorityYear="2021" box="[955,1074,1837,1862]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Heza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="376" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="graziae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B95FEAA5B937E50439E8886DFBE6F88B" box="[955,1074,1837,1862]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="376">H. graziae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B95FEAA5B937E5043E69886DFB41F88A" bold="true" box="[1082,1173,1837,1863]" pageId="10" pageNumber="376">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26C57DEB937E5043E69886DFB41F88A" box="[1082,1173,1837,1863]" pageId="10" pageNumber="376" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, the median process of the pygophore has a shorter, thicker stem and the apex and recurved fold are distinctly broader. 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B4D34B937E5043E838811FAA7F8A7" authority="Swanson, 2021" authorityName="Swanson" authorityYear="2021" box="[1232,1395,1872,1898]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Heza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="376" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridipes" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B95FEAA5B937E5043E838811FAA7F8A7" box="[1232,1395,1872,1898]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="376">Heza viridipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B95FEAA5B937E5043F288811FF1CF842" bold="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="376">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26C57DEB937E5043F288811FF1CF842" pageId="10" pageNumber="376" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
also differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B4D34B937E5043BC08835FDE9F843" authorityName="Maldonado" authorityYear="1976" box="[403,573,1908,1934]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Heza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="376" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubromarga">
<emphasis id="B95FEAA5B937E5043BC08835FDE9F843" box="[403,573,1908,1934]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="376">H. rubromarga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in that the stem of the median process of the pygophore is slenderer and the lateral margins diverge apically. As mentioned under 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B4D34B937E50438A788D9FCBFF87F" authority="Swanson, 2021" authorityName="Swanson" authorityYear="2021" box="[756,875,1945,1970]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Heza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="376" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="graziae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B95FEAA5B937E50438A788D9FCBFF87F" box="[756,875,1945,1970]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="376">H. graziae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B95FEAA5B937E504392088D9FC1AF87E" bold="true" box="[883,974,1945,1971]" pageId="10" pageNumber="376">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26C57DEB937E504392088D9FC1AF87E" box="[883,974,1945,1971]" pageId="10" pageNumber="376" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBA4B46B937E504398E88D8FB16F87E" author="Maldonado" box="[989,1218,1944,1971]" pageId="10" pageNumber="376" pagination="403 - 433" refId="ref8630" refString="Maldonado C., J. (1976) The genus Heza (Hemiptera: Reduviidae). Journal of Agriculture of the University of Puerto Rico, 60 (3), 403 - 433. https: // doi. org / 10.46429 / jaupr. v 60 i 3.10533" type="journal article" year="1976">Maldonado’s (1976)</bibRefCitation>
characterization of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B4D34B937E5043AC488FDFEFBF81B" baseAuthorityName="Kirby" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[151,303,1981,2006]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Heza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="376" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perarmata">
<emphasis id="B95FEAA5B937E5043AC488FDFEFBF81B" box="[151,303,1981,2006]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="376">H. perarmata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears to be erroneous, and the specimen pictured clearly differs 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B4D34B937E5043E4F88FDFB74F81B" authority="Swanson, 2021" authorityName="Swanson" authorityYear="2021" box="[1052,1184,1980,2006]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Heza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="376" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridipes" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B95FEAA5B937E5043E4F88FDFB74F81B" box="[1052,1184,1980,2006]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="376">H. viridipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B95FEAA5B937E5043EF488FDFAD5F81A" bold="true" box="[1191,1281,1981,2007]" pageId="10" pageNumber="376">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26C57DEB937E5043EF488FDFAD5F81A" box="[1191,1281,1981,2007]" pageId="10" pageNumber="376" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in possessing an aciculate median process of the pygophore.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9436B7B936E5053A948FD7FE16FE8C" blockId="11.[151,1437,151,321]" pageId="11" pageNumber="377">
The median process of the pygophore of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B4D34B936E50538CE8FD7FCF6FF7C" authority="Swanson, 2021" authorityName="Swanson" authorityYear="2021" box="[669,802,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Heza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="377" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridipes" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B95FEAA5B936E50538CE8FD7FCF6FF7C" box="[669,802,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="377">H. viridipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B95FEAA5B936E50539788FD7FC52FF7C" bold="true" box="[811,902,151,177]" pageId="11" pageNumber="377">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26C57DEB936E50539788FD7FC52FF7C" box="[811,902,151,177]" pageId="11" pageNumber="377" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
also is superficially similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B4D34B936E5053EB48FD7FA9FFF7C" authorityName="Maldonado" authorityYear="1976" box="[1255,1355,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Heza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="377" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubra">
<emphasis id="B95FEAA5B936E5053EB48FD7FA9FFF7C" box="[1255,1355,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="377">H. rubra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but in addition to differing in the same way as 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B4D34B936E50538318FFBFCD9FF18" authorityName="Maldonado" authorityYear="1976" box="[610,781,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Heza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="377" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubromarga">
<emphasis id="B95FEAA5B936E50538318FFBFCD9FF18" box="[610,781,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="377">H. rubromarga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the apical margin is less convex, and the recurved apical fold is narrower. 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B4D34B936E5053B048F9FFE0CFF34" authorityName="Maldonado" authorityYear="1976" box="[343,472,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Heza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="377" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubra">
<emphasis id="B95FEAA5B936E5053B048F9FFE0CFF34" box="[343,472,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="377">Heza rubra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also possesses medium-sized, apically blunted armature of the anterior pronotal lobe. Lastly, the general habitus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B4D34B936E5053BB18E43FDAEFED0" baseAuthorityName="Lichtenstein" baseAuthorityYear="1796" box="[482,634,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Heza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="377" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ephippium">
<emphasis id="B95FEAA5B936E5053BB18E43FDAEFED0" box="[482,634,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="377">H. ephippium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
looks similar, but the armature of the anterior pronotal lobe is mediumsized and apically blunted.
</paragraph>
